# vendored.sha256 — divergence pin for the VENDORED reachability analyzer
# sources (M45 Wave 3, C4a). This file is IDENTICAL in both repos:
#   backend: sbomhub/apps/api/internal/service/reachability/
#   CLI:     sbomhub-cli/internal/reachability/
#
# Each data line below is "<sha256>  <filename>", where <sha256> is the
# SHA-256 of the file's NORMALISED BODY. Normalisation == stripVendorHeader()
# in vendor_sync_test.go: the `package <name>` clause line, then everything
# from the first non-blank / non-`//`-comment line after it to EOF. The
# header comment blocks (which intentionally differ between the two copies)
# are excluded, so this pin is byte-identical in both repos.
#
# WHAT THIS PIN CATCHES / DOES NOT CATCH (read before trusting it):
#   * CATCHES (single-repo, no sibling checkout needed): editing a vendored
#     file's body WITHOUT updating this pin. TestVendoredAnalyzerMatchesPin
#     recomputes the hashes and fails on mismatch — tamper-evident even in
#     the CLI's solo CI where the cross-repo byte comparison is skipped.
#   * DOES NOT CATCH: the two repos silently diverging when BOTH sides update
#     file+pin together but to DIFFERENT content. Each repo's self-check would
#     still pass. True cross-repo equivalence is only proven by
#     TestVendoredAnalyzer{InSyncWithBackend,InSyncWithCLI}, which byte-compare
#     the two checked-out copies and require the sbom-all workspace layout
#     (they skip in single-repo CI).
#   In short: SHA pin = per-repo tamper-evidence; workspace test = real
#   cross-repo equivalence. Neither alone is complete; together they are
#   defence in depth.
#
# To update after an intentional analyzer change: apply the SAME diff to BOTH
# copies, then regenerate this file in BOTH repos (the test failure message
# prints the expected vs actual hashes to paste back in).
9ac0b6d03cc3176de7f3b2e8a7e178f127c2f52171be708b51d8b368a33b2b0e  types.go
2e15a80375250356c56f8003c7da72a20ff4d9b040aeec8f6f891c80f0acdd26  go_analyzer.go
edf036df2f10982de82d2c136a2d1e82e51f205c40e8ec2dbd3f7accecedef26  npm_analyzer.go
